-- Thailand Stocks: Nation Broadcasting, PTT Exploration, Sri Trang
-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 2012-06-07T09:55:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-07/thailand-stocks-nation-broadcasting-ptt-exploration-sri-trang.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in Thailand  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Bangkok.  The  SET Index (SET)  rose 0.1 percent to 1,118.53, its second day
of gains.  Nation Broadcasting Corp. Pcl (NBC)  , a broadcaster of
satellite televisions, climbed 0.9 percent to 4.44 baht. The
company will recover revenue loss from two television programs,
President Adisak Limprungpatanakij, told an investor meeting
today. The company has moved two television programs to its own
satellite television channels after a contract with state-
controlled MCOT Pcl expired this month, he said.  PTT Exploration & Production Pcl (PTTEP)  , the nation’s
only publicly traded oil explorer, advanced 1.3 percent to 159.5
baht, the highest close since May 22. PTTEP Canada International
Finance Ltd., PTT Exploration’s unit, is marketing $500 million
of 30-year bonds to yield about 6.5 percent, according to a
person familiar with the matter. PTT Exploration is a guarantor
for the bond.  Sri Trang Agro-Industry Pcl (STA)  , Thailand’s largest
rubber producer, gained 1.4 percent to 14.4 baht. Rubber futures
gained as much as 4.2 percent, the biggest climb since Jan. 17,
to 251 yen a kilogram ($3,165 a metric ton) before settling at
243.4 yen on the Tokyo Commodity Exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
